  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Women, Migrants and Host Communities in Egypt to Cope with the Impacts of COVID-19 through Mental Health and Psychosocial Support Services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project addresses the urgent need for not only the urgently requested provision of medical equipment for the containment of the COVID-19 spread but also the much-needed mental health and psychosocial support services to stranded migrants, refugees, and host communities in the areas of Cairo and Alexandria, with a focus on the vulnerable groups, especially women and children. It also aims at the crucial provision of technical and financial support to Egypt&#x2019;s National Response Plan to COVID-19, given the identification of the alarmingly fast deterioration of physical and mental health of the population since the beginning of the pandemic.</narrative>
  </description>
